Grind scallions, garlic, and sesame seeds in a small food processor or with a mortar and pestle. Stir in soy sauce, sugar, water, sesame oil, and vinegar. Pour into shallow dish. Add beef; turn slices to coat. Cover and chill 45 minutes. Preheat grill to high for direct heat. Remove beef from marinade (discard marinade). Grill 2 to 3 minutes, turning once.